fields.text_1: I specialise in Python / Javascript - Django ,Flask backends with ReactJs, Redux Front ends, I also have experience with Node.js, and AngularJs. I've recently been working a lot with google home and Alexa bots to make various chat bots.
fields.text_2: My background was building pipelines in VFX using python and various Databases both SQL and NOSQL and UIs in 3D applications. In my spare time I experiment with new technologies such as Data Science and Machine learning and do Gymnastics and acrobatics with my friends and partner.

A multi-threaded ray tracing renderer built in C++
A node.js chat room build to learn websockets so I could build a simple chat room server.

Technologies used:
- Node.js
- React
- DialogFlow
- Firebase
- Python
- TensorFlow
- Magenta

This is google voice experiment which can be seen on the official google site:
https://experiments.withgoogle.com/collection/voice

I was responsible for all work on the project both front end and backend, building the React Front end and the Dialog flow / firebase powered chat bot backend. This is web app that will allow you to use the Speech Recognition web API and it is also a google home app you can access using a google home device. A user can provide 3 animals and the web app will combine them to produce an animation combining the animals. Python and machine learning was used to produce a sound effect of the animals mixed together also.
